HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 722
By Hemmer
A RESOLUTION to recognize and honor Wade Cowan upon his
receipt of the President's Award from the
Montgomery Bell Academy Mock Trial team.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Wade Cowan, who has distinguished
himself as a citizen of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Cowan was recently honored with the President's Award from the
Montgomery Bell Academy (MBA) Mock Trial team at the National Bar Association's Annual
Meeting and Banquet, a most befitting honor that recognizes his exceptional legal and
educational contributions; and
WHEREAS, Wade Cowan is a Nashville-based attorney, who specializes in legal
services and labor law; he is a 1974 alumnus of Montgomery Bell Academy and has devoted
more than forty years of astute service as a mock trial coach for high school students
throughout Nashville; and
WHEREAS, for twenty-five years, Mr. Cowan has directed the MBA program, during
which time the Mock Trial team earned nineteen City Championship titles and several State
titles; this year, he led the MBA team to its first National High School Mock Trial Championship
in Phoenix, Arizona, a victory that followed the school's sixth overall Tennessee state title win in
March; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Cowan is wholly committed to the noble precepts of student success
that have earned Tennessee recognition as the Volunteer State, and it is appropriate that he be
specially recognized on this momentous occasion; now, therefore,
HJR0722
010815
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Wade Cowan upon his receipt of the President's
Award from the Montgomery Bell Academy Mock Trial team, extending to him our best wishes
for continued success and happiness in all his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
